.How would you use the docker run command with -it, -e, -v, and --name to:
•	Set an environment variable APP_ENV=production.	
•	Bind a local directory /app/data to /data inside the container.	
•	Name the container my_app.	


PS C:\Users\Administrator> mkdir C:\app\data                    


    Directory: C:\app


Mode                 LastWriteTime         Length Name
----                 -------------         ------ ----
d-----          4/5/2026  11:03 AM                data


PS C:\Users\Administrator> docker run -it -e APP_ENV=production -v C:\app\data:/data --name my_app ubuntu
root@53ff2df4de8c:/# echo $APP_ENV
production
root@53ff2df4de8c:/# ls/data
bash: ls/data: No such file or directory
root@53ff2df4de8c:/# nano file.txt
